{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's why I remembered Weinreb all of a sudden, even though I knew about him, and he was-- basically it was a sort of-- more than anybody else it was a whole-- it was a whole big thing about him because he was accused of dealing with the German authorities, you know, and selling Jews.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he claims just the opposite, that he was trying to save Jews, and it was never resolved really.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he-- this gentleman made me-- he wrote books in German, huge books like this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I don't read German that well, you know, so I started to read.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then I decided to-- you know, they were very self-serving books that tried to explain his-- his point of view.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And had they been in English, I probably would have had read them, but being in German, I decided you know, I didn't-- I couldn't be bothered.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I brought them back to him, and-- but I remember then-- then I also asked somebody else about him, Professor [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know if anybody ever heard of him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He's one of the foremost authorities on the-- And he knew about him also, so he knows-- knows more about Eastern European people like [INAUDIBLE] He knows more about than what he knew about him.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he also said, look.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's difficult to judge from where we are today whether they were right or wrong what they did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But anyway, to go back to my story, we-- so he was called to go to-- on a train, which I didn't know at the time was going to Sobibor, together with my aunt and-- and my cousin in 1942.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This must have been in June, July.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I think I have the exact date.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I gave you the date, I think, when he died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'43, Yeah, not '42, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Did I say '42?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah, '43, it must be '43.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think it was June or July '43, and they were killed in Sobibor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he had made arrangements for us to stay in an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Westerbork was run in a way-- if you know the story about Thereisenstadt, Terezin, it-- it was in a way similar.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even though it was a transit camp, Theresienstadt also was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were all sort of things going on inside the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, it was-- For instance, the orphanage was run by a gentleman called Yehoshua Berenbaum with his wife, who had been in Westerbork since 1939.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Westerbork had been established by the Dutch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They used it for German refugees who came after the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they didn't know what to do with them, so in the end, they put them in Westerbork, which was way out, like I said, in-- like I said, in [? left ?] field.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And people didn't know where it was, and that's where they kept them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they ran their own camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In those days, they ran the camp themselves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a Dutch police commandant in charge, but there was no barbed wire around it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They could leave, if they-- but they couldn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They had nowhere to go, so they stayed there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he was one of those people who had been there from the very beginning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, first of all, the poor lady, Miep, who had to supply them, had to find food for eight people who were living illegally.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Secondly, if you were caught, everybody was caught.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So most families split up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, they had the parents in one place and the children in another place, or even-- they split off even more than that.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First of all, there were two-- two reasons.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Number one, it was easier for the people who were hiding them, and also for this other reason that if somebody got caught, maybe somebody else would survive.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So for this reason, you had the orphans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, many of them were-- were not originally orphans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But their parents had been caught, or they had been caught.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and they had nobody to stay with.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, in Westerbork, all together, we were privileged that we were allowed to receive parcels from the outside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- so Dutch people would send us parcels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I know my sister and myself got a lot of parcels from friends, who-- some of my uncles were sending those parcels, and they, of course, went to the orphanage, like everybody else's.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were fairly well, as far as food was concerned, fairly well taken care of.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He wouldn't-- he wouldn't give in, you know, so every week some children went, which was very sad.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and we were one of the few who weren't called for quite a while.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
